		<div>I have readen many nice things in these posts.<br />
<br />
My whishes :<br />
<br />
<b>1) Please give us diversity ! </b><br />
<br />
In the past, when we had to choose between alternatives, it has usually been a waste (specialization: we all took the same, Gods : you see what I mean , faction : we don t care but maybe cov/geant long ago, DoN side : even evil classes are on &quot;good&quot; side mostly).<br />
<br />
But I still like the idea of diversity for a given class. I would like to see a choice between lines of AA, balanced enough so not all players take the same one.<br />
Some ideas : not sure about the content, just examples :<br />
<br />
Line &quot;efficiency&quot; :<br />
- less mana cost // decap evocation<br />
- less resist<br />
- an AA with free mana low DD (1000 damage) with low reuse time<br />
<br />
Line &quot;damages&quot; :<br />
- bonus on DD<br />
- bonus on critik rate<br />
- an AA with free mana high DD (5000 damage) with long reuse time<br />
<br />
Line &quot;subltlety&quot; :<br />
- less agro (must be noticeable)<br />
- fixed IvU or rogue's like sos<br />
- an AA with free mana dot <br />
<br />
A hard long boring quest would allow a change of choice after you made one.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>2) Mana burn/blaze</b><br />
<br />
Wizard still like the flashy big boum :)<br />
<br />
- Would like an AA with a little chance (1% ?) to critik on manablaze/burn<br />
- Would like line of AA with a little chance (5%?) to lower mana cost, or get a random capped cost for same damage</div>
