				Here's an idea for a future spell line:<br />
<br />
A &quot;Damage Sword&quot; in the same vein of Damage Shields.<br />
<br />
Where Mages are the masters of the DS and even &quot;burst&quot; DSs out there for Druids and Mages, they can keep that field. Even clerics with their reverse damage shield where the mob takes damage for every swing it makes. Why not have us reflect the cleric, like we have many times in the past? (The whole destruction/healing mirror).<br />
<br />
I would like to see a new line for wizards where the mob takes damage for every swing made against it. (At least, I'm fairly sure this doesn't exist yet.)<br />
<br />
Call the spell something like &quot;Burn Armor&quot;, &quot;Festering Fire&quot; or &quot;Burden of Lightning&quot;. *shrug*<br />
Have it cost perhaps... 100-200 mana.<br />
And then every time a successful melee hit is made against the mob, it takes an extra 2-5+ damage or whatever is deemed proper. It wouldn't stack up like other DSs though, so only one on the mob at a time.<br />
<br />
This would give the grouping wizard utility, the soloing wizard wouldn't be helped much if at all and the raiding wizard would still be able to focus soley on nuking with one wizard designated for this spell. Could also make it retro-active and give it to lower level wizards in a smaller form if they pull a Luclin and add it in like familiars.<br />
<br />
And of course, it would be aggro free like DSs, still keeping in the &quot;detrimental&quot; form of the wizard and something new without stepping on any toes.<br />
<br />
Just an idea.
			
